Audit Trail Q&A System for Internal Finance Teams
Enterprise Project Blueprint & Development Roadmap
Project Vision
Build an enterprise-grade AI audit assistant rather than a simple RAG demo. The system should resemble software used by internal finance and audit teams, with a modular backend, secure authentication, explainable AI, and a complete audit workflow.
Development Sequence (Recommended)
Phase 1: Requirements Analysis
• Define business requirements
• Identify users (Auditor, Finance Manager, Admin)
• Define functional & non-functional requirements
• Create use cases

Phase 2: High-Level Design (HLD)
• Overall architecture
• Technology stack
• Service interactions
• Data flow

Phase 3: Low-Level Design (LLD)
• Folder structure
• Database schema
• API contracts
• Class/module design

Phase 4: Database Design
• PostgreSQL schema
• Relationships
• Seed synthetic ledger and audit data

Phase 5: Backend Foundation
• FastAPI project
• JWT Authentication
• Role-based authorization
• Logging
• Exception handling
• Configuration management

Phase 6: Ledger Service
• Search & filter transactions
• Pagination
• Sorting
• Validation

Phase 7: Rule Engine
• Duplicate detection
• Threshold violations
• Round-number detection
• Vendor-account mismatch
• Split payments
• Benford's Law
• Risk scoring

Phase 8: RAG Layer
• Chunk policy documents
• Create embeddings
• Store in Qdrant
• Retrieve policies and similar audit cases

Phase 9: MCP Server
• query_ledger()
• flag_discrepancy()
• generate_audit_note()
• retrieve_policy()
• retrieve_similar_cases()

Phase 10: LLM Integration
• Prompt templates
• Claude API
• JSON structured outputs
• Audit note generation

Phase 11: Frontend
• Login
• Dashboard
• Ledger Explorer
• Audit Workspace
• Policy Search
• Reports
• Admin Panel

Phase 12: Testing
• Unit Tests
• Integration Tests
• API Testing
• RAG Evaluation

Phase 13: Deployment
• Docker
• Docker Compose
• Nginx
• CI/CD
• Monitoring
